# Node.js 2012 Call For Proposals

So, you are interested in giving a talk at the most awesome Node.js
conference in Europe?
And what better way to submit a talk proposal than via GitHub!
CFP closes September 20th.

http://nodejsconf.it 
@nodejsconfit

  
## Here is what to do

1. Fork this repository
2. Copy the sample folder `example/` to `your_name-talk_name`
3. Edit the `proposal.json` file and type a good description about your talk
   and about yourself
4. Create a pull request of your fork

You can add any type of assets to support your proposal inside your
folder.
When a talk gets accepted we will press the lovely green merge button.
